P_middleofeyes_to_imu_oxr.note: I didn't have time to do this the right way. You can come up with this using https://quaternions.online/: it's nominally a -15 degree rotation on the X axis (in CAD, the calibration camera is rotated -25 degrees and the ProW is rotated -40), then a -90 degree rotation on the Y axis (because of how they mounted the IMU). In a more ideal situation I'd've written a calibration app to do this for us.

desc: for each member of `grids->{left, right}`, `grid` is a mapping from UV to bearing coordinates - rows are Y-axis, columns are X-axis, (0,0) UV is top-left of the screen and top-left of this array.
